*As the* Planning Poker Development Team
*I want* to join an existing room using a shared link and enter a display name
*So that* I can participate in the planning session and be visible to other participants

*Acceptance Criteria*
- AC01: Visiting a room URL shows a display name entry prompt before the user enters the room
- AC02: The display name field enforces a 1 to 32 character limit after trimming whitespace, with a clear message shown if the constraint is not met
- AC03: Submitting a valid display name connects the user to the room and navigates them to the main room view
- AC04: The user's display name is visible to other participants already in the room
- AC05: If the room ID in the URL does not exist, the user becomes the host of a new room with that ID

*Out of Scope*
- Room ID generation and initial redirect (covered by AIA-62)
- The voting interface and participant list details (separate stories)
- Changing display name after joining the room

*Technical Notes*
- Open a WebSocket connection to the backend using the room ID from the URL query parameter and the entered display name
- Store the `userId` from the backend's `welcome` message to identify the current user in subsequent `state` messages
- Replace the full room state on every `state` message received — do not merge
- Backend WebSocket endpoint: `wss://planning-poker-backend-ymq7.onrender.com/ws?room=<roomId>&name=<displayName>`

*Testing Notes*
- Verify the display name prompt is shown when visiting a `/?room=<id>` URL
- Verify that submitting an empty name or a name exceeding 32 characters is rejected with a user-facing message
- Verify that submitting a valid name navigates the user to the main room view
- Verify the joined user appears in the participant list visible to others in the room
